{"id": "duc04-testb-6:2#7", "contents": "International medical workers have documented the severe compounding of food shortages by a breakdown in public health services. Basic water purification systems are idle due to a lack of essential ingredients like chlorine, leaving many people with severe diarrhea that prevents them from absorbing what little food they have. The North Korean dictatorship has slowly granted increased access to international aid groups, allowing a clearer picture of the hunger crisis to emerge. Researchers and aid workers have not found evidence of cannibalism or starving children dying by the roadside, but instead a population weakened by malnutrition, where colds and stomach flus can quickly turn lethal."}
